'''Marcos Llorente Moreno''' (born 30 January 1995) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] or [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Atlético Madrid]] and the [[Spain national football team|Spain national team]].

Developed at [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]], he appeared in 39 competitive matches over three seasons, also serving a loan at [[Deportivo Alavés|Alavés]]. He signed with [[Atlético Madrid]] in June 2019, winning the [[2020–21 La Liga]] while being deployed in several positions.

Llorente made his full debut for [[Spain national football team|Spain]] in 2020, and was part of the squads at [[UEFA Euro 2020]] and two [[FIFA World Cup]]s.

==Club career==
===Real Madrid===
[[File:Marcos Llorente.JPG|thumb|upright|Llorente playing for [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in 2015]]
Born in [[Madrid]], Llorente joined [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]'s youth setup in 2008, aged 13.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defensacentral.com/la_fabrica/119889-marcos-llorente-empieza-llamar-puerta-reportaje/|title=Marcos Llorente empieza a llamar a la puerta|trans-title=Marcos Llorente starts calling the door|publisher=Defensa Central|first=Diego|last=Vargas|language=es|date=24 February 2015|access-date=17 October 2015}}</ref> In July 2014, after impressing with the ''Juvenil'' squad, he was promoted straight to [[Real Madrid Castilla|the reserves]] by manager [[Zinedine Zidane]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2014/07/25/futbol/equipos/real_madrid/1406303675.html|title=Flechazo con Marcos Llorente|trans-title=Love at first sight with Marcos Llorente|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|first=Pablo|last=Polo|language=es|date=25 July 2014|access-date=17 October 2015}}</ref>

On 24 August 2014, Llorente made his senior debut, starting in a 2–1 away loss against [[Atlético Madrid B]] in the [[Segunda División B]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2014/08/2-1-castilla-let-the-three-points-slip-against-atletico-b|title=2–1: Castilla let the three points slip against Atlético B|publisher=Real Madrid CF|language=es|date=24 August 2014|access-date=17 October 2015}}</ref> He appeared in 25 matches during [[2014–15 Segunda División B|the campaign]], totalling 1,637 minutes of action.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.noticiasdealava.eus/alaves/2016/08/09/marcos-llorente-llegara-cedido/333870.html|title=Marcos Llorente llegará cedido|trans-title=Marcos Llorente will arrive on loan|newspaper=Noticias de Álava|first=José Luis|last=Del Campo|language=es|date=9 August 2016|access-date=23 June 2021}}</ref>

Llorente spent the 2015 pre-season with the first team, appearing in [[Friendly (association football)|friendlies]] against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], [[Inter Milan]] and [[Vålerenga Fotball|Vålerenga]]. He made his professional – and [[La Liga]] – debut on 17 October of that year, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Mateo Kovačić]] in the 3–0 home win over [[Levante UD|Levante]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2015_16/la-liga/jornada_8/rma_lev/|title=Antibalas Keylor y tres fogonazos|trans-title=Bulletproof Keylor and three flashes|newspaper=Marca|first=Rubén|last=Jiménez|language=es|date=17 October 2015|access-date=17 October 2015}}</ref>

On 10 August 2016, Llorente was [[Loan (association football)|loaned]] to [[Deportivo Alavés|Alavés]] for [[2016–17 La Liga|the season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deportivoalaves.com/noticia/marcos-llorente-calidad-y-vision-de-juego-para-el-centro-del-campo|title=Marcos Llorente, calidad y visión de juego para el centro del campo|trans-title=Marcos Llorente, quality and vision for the midfield|publisher=Deportivo Alavés|language=es|date=10 August 2016|access-date=13 February 2021}}</ref> On 10 September, he featured the full 90 minutes in a 2–1 victory at [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://realidadblanca.com/2016/09/11/marcos-llorente-se-luce-camp-nou/|title=Marcos Llorente se luce en el Camp Nou|trans-title=Marcos Llorente shows his stuff at the Camp Nou|publisher=Realidad Blanca|first=Ignacio|last=Parrón Estévez|language=es|date=11 September 2016|access-date=11 September 2016|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160913052734/http://realidadblanca.com/2016/09/11/marcos-llorente-se-luce-camp-nou/|archive-date=13 September 2016}}</ref>

On 23 September 2017, Llorente's contract was extended until 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2017/09/marcos-llorentes-contract-extension|title=Ceremony to mark Marcos Llorente's contract renewal|publisher=Real Madrid CF|date=23 September 2017|access-date=24 September 2017}}</ref> He made one appearance in [[2017–18 UEFA Champions League|that campaign]]'s [[UEFA Champions League]],<ref name=RCN>{{cite web|url=https://www.rcnradio.com/deportes/asi-llegan-las-plantillas-de-real-madrid-y-liverpool-la-final-de-la-champions|title=Así llegan Real Madrid y Liverpool a la final de la Champions|trans-title=That is how Real Madrid and Liverpool arrive to the Champions final|publisher=[[RCN Radio]]|language=es|date=25 May 2018|access-date=29 May 2018}}</ref> when Madrid won their third consecutive and 13th overall title in the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0245-0e98d7318379-716954065574-1000--madrid-beat-liverpool-to-complete-hat-trick/|title=Madrid beat Liverpool to complete hat-trick|publisher=UEFA|date=26 May 2018|access-date=28 May 2018}}</ref>

Llorente had played just 11 minutes in [[2018–19 La Liga|2018–19]] until late November, when [[Casemiro]] dropped out with an ankle injury.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2018/12/21/5c1ccedce5fdea306d8b4594.html|title=Battle between Casemiro and Llorente begins|newspaper=Marca|first1=Pablo|last1=Polo|first2=Oliver|last2=French|date=21 December 2018|access-date=23 March 2026}}</ref> Interim coach [[Santiago Solari]] handed the former his first starts as a [[defensive midfielder]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.seattletimes.com/sports/casemiro-getting-back-to-his-best-with-madrid/|title=Casemiro getting back to his best with Madrid|newspaper=[[The Seattle Times]]|first=Joseph|last=Wilson|date=20 January 2019|access-date=22 March 2026}}</ref> and he scored his first competitive goal for the team on 22 December, the second in the 4–1 defeat of [[Al Ain FC|Al Ain]] in [[2018 FIFA Club World Cup|the final]] of the [[FIFA Club World Cup]] to earn him [[player of the match]] honours.<ref name=FCWC>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/mundial-de-clubes/cronica/2018/12/22/5c1e81a2e5fdea02688b4580.html|title=El Madrid agranda su leyenda|trans-title=Madrid largen their legend|newspaper=Marca|first=José María|last=Rodríguez|language=es|date=22 December 2018|access-date=22 December 2018|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191008171528/https://www.marca.com/futbol/mundial-de-clubes/cronica/2018/12/22/5c1e81a2e5fdea02688b4580.html|archive-date=8 October 2019}}</ref>

At the start of 2019, Llorente was sidelined with [[Adductor longus muscle|adductor]] problems. During his recovery, Solari was replaced by Zidane, who preferred to use [[Federico Valverde]] in the holding midfielder role;<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/1939079/2020/07/30/llorente-marcos-atletico-madrid-liverpool/|title=Llorente, Atletico’s new star who named his dog Anfield after winning there|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|first=Dermot|last=Corrigan|date=30 July 2020|access-date=22 March 2026}}</ref> additionally, Zidane stated that the player needed "more first-team minutes" in order to improve.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-espana.net/2019/04/15/real-madrid-to-loan-out-marcos-llorente-zinedine-zidane|title=Real Madrid to loan out Marcos Llorente – Zinedine Zidane|publisher=Football España|first=Colin|last=Millar|date=15 April 2019|access-date=22 March 2026}}</ref>

===Atlético Madrid===
On 20 June 2019, Llorente was signed by [[Madrid derby|local rivals]] [[Atlético Madrid]] on a five-year contract for a reported fee of £35&nbsp;million;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/agreement-over-the-transfer-of-marcos-llorente|title=Agreement over the transfer of Marcos Llorente|publisher=Atlético Madrid|date=20 June 2019|access-date=20 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2019/06/official-announcement-marcos-llorente|title=Official announcement: Marcos Llorente|publisher=Real Madrid CF|date=20 June 2019|access-date=20 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11838/11745511/marcos-llorente-agrees-to-join-atletico-madrid-from-real-madrid|title=Marcos Llorente agrees to join Atletico Madrid from Real Madrid|publisher=[[Sky Sports]]|date=21 June 2019|access-date=19 July 2019}}</ref> he was given shirt number 14, previously worn by [[Rodri (footballer, born 1996)|Rodri]] who left for Manchester City during the same [[transfer window]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/37509930/rodri-man-city-club-record-signing-plays-busquets-classic-guardiola-pivot-midfielder|title=Rodri, Man City's club-record signing, plays like Busquets and is a classic Guardiola 'pivot' midfielder|publisher=[[ESPN]]|first=Sid|last=Lowe|date=4 July 2019|access-date=23 March 2026}}</ref> He made his official debut on 18 August, playing 25 minutes in the 1–0 home win against [[Getafe CF|Getafe]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report?gameId=550606|title=Atleti beat Getafe as both teams finish with 10 men|publisher=ESPN|date=18 August 2019|access-date=21 August 2019}}</ref>

In the first half of his [[2019–20 La Liga|debut campaign]], Llorente was among the Atlético squad members with the fewest playing time.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://as.com/futbol/2019/12/07/primera/1575758342_935130.html|title=Marcos Llorente juega menos en el Atlético que en el Madrid|trans-title=Marcos Llorente plays less at Atlético than he did at Madrid|newspaper=[[Diario AS]]|first=Sergio|last=Picos|language=es|date=7 December 2019|access-date=23 March 2026}}</ref> He became a regular starter in January 2020, scoring his first goal on 14 February when he put his team ahead in a 2–2 draw at [[Valencia CF|Valencia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.in/football/report?gameId=550375|title=Valencia come from behind to draw with Atletico Madrid in La Liga thriller|publisher=ESPN|date=14 February 2020|access-date=18 July 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://quepasamedia.com/noticias/deportes/el-retorno-al-origen-de-llorente/|title=El retorno al origen de Llorente|trans-title=Llorente's return to his roots|newspaper=[[Qué Pasa (newspaper)|Qué Pasa]]|first=Iñaki|last=Dufour|language=es|date=21 February 2025|access-date=23 March 2026}}</ref>

On 11 March 2020, during [[Extra time (association football)|extra time]] of the [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League|Champions League round-of-16 tie]] away to defending champions [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], Llorente scored twice to tie the match 2–2 after replacing [[Diego Costa]] early into the second half, in an eventual 3–2 victory and qualification.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/liverpool-vs-atletico-madrid-live-score-champions-league-result-a4385036.html?amp|title=Liverpool crash out of Champions League to Atletico Madrid – LIVE! Latest news and result reaction|newspaper=[[Evening Standard]]|first=Tom|last=Doyle|date=11 March 2020|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> On 17 June, he came off the bench in the 63rd minute to be named man of the match in the league game at [[CA Osasuna|Osasuna]], scoring a solo goal and later [[Assist (association football)|assisting]] twice in the 5–0 rout.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://as.com/futbol/2020/06/17/primera/1592416179_639585.html|title=Goleada de Champions|trans-title=Champions rout|newspaper=Diario AS|first=Patricia|last=Cazón|language=es|date=17 June 2020|access-date=23 June 2020}}</ref>

Llorente scored a career-best 12 times in [[2020–21 La Liga|2020–21]] (second-best in the squad behind [[Luis Suárez]]'s 21), adding 11 assists as the ''Colchoneros'' were crowned champions after a seven-year wait; in the process, he became the club's first player to register double digits in both categories since [[Diego Forlán]] in [[2008–09 La Liga|2008–09]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.elespanol.com/deportes/futbol/20210522/suarez-marcos-llorente-barca-madrid-liga-atletico/577193242_0.html|title=Suárez y Marcos Llorente, el 'regalo' del Barça y el 'descarte' del Madrid que dieron La Liga al Atlético|trans-title=Suárez and Marcos Llorente, the Barça 'gift' and the Madrid 'surplus' that gave La Liga to Atlético|newspaper=[[El Español]]|first=Jorge|last=Pacheco|language=es|date=22 May 2021|access-date=21 April 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/apuestas-deportivas/marcos-llorente-lider-simeone-12004970|title=Marcos Llorente, un líder para Simeone|trans-title=Marcos Llorente, a leader to Simeone|newspaper=[[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]]|language=es|date=24 August 2021|access-date=21 April 2022}}</ref>

==International career==
Llorente earned his first [[Cap (association football)|cap]] for the [[Spain national under-21 football team|Spain under-21 side]] on 10 October 2016, featuring the entire 5–0 home defeat of [[Estonia national under-21 football team|Estonia]] in the [[2017 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]] [[2017 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification|qualifiers]], in [[Pontevedra]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://futbol.as.com/futbol/2016/09/30/seleccion/1475231824_071710.html|title=Asensio regresa a la Sub-21 y debuta Marcos Llorente|trans-title=Asensio returns to the Under-21s and Marcos Llorente makes debut|newspaper=Diario AS|first=Aritz|last=Gabilondo|language=es|date=30 September 2016|access-date=12 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://futbol.as.com/futbol/2016/10/10/seleccion/1476125525_834402.html|title=La Rojita golea y se jugará ir a la Eurocopa en la repesca|trans-title=''Rojita'' rout to fight for Eurocup berth in the play-offs|newspaper=Diario AS|last=Gabilondo|first=Aritz|language=es|date=10 October 2016|access-date=12 January 2017}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Spain national football team|senior squad]] in November 2020, for a friendly with the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] and [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League qualifiers]] against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] and [[Germany national football team|Germany]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://en.as.com/en/2020/11/06/football/1604668097_282164.html|title=Spain squad: Morata, Koke return, Marcos Llorente gets first call-up|newspaper=Diario AS|date=6 November 2020|access-date=11 November 2020|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201106150731/https://en.as.com/en/2020/11/06/football/1604668097_282164.html|archive-date=6 November 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/netherlands-vs-spain-betting-tips-latest-odds-team-news/tjhv3jq8pfaj1og5l3sejwgoq|title=Netherlands vs Spain betting tips: Latest odds, team news, preview and predictions|publisher=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|first=Phil|last=Kitromilides|date=11 November 2020|access-date=11 November 2020}}</ref> He made his first appearance against the first opponent, replacing [[Sergio Canales]] for the last 18 minutes of the 1–1 draw in [[Amsterdam]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/seleccion/holanda-vs-espana/cronica/2020/11/11/5fac304746163fb5478b4640.html|title=Las chapas de España se quedan a medias|trans-title=Spain's ''chapas'' go halfway|newspaper=Marca|first=José Luis|last=Hurtado|language=es|date=11 November 2020|access-date=11 November 2020}}</ref>

On 24 May 2021, Llorente was included in Spain's [[UEFA Euro 2020 squads#Spain|24-man squad]] for [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12315756/sergio-ramos-left-out-of-spain-squad-for-euro-2020-as-luis-enrique-snubs-real-madrid-players|title=Sergio Ramos left out of Spain squad for Euro 2020 as Luis Enrique snubs Real Madrid players|publisher=Sky Sports|date=24 May 2021|access-date=25 May 2021}}</ref> He was deployed as [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] during the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-espana.net/2021/06/14/spain-starting-sweden-confirmed-olmo|title=Spain starting XI to face Sweden confirmed as Luis Enrique starts Dani Olmo|publisher=Football España|first=Jamie|last=Kemble|date=14 June 2021|access-date=20 June 2021}}</ref>

Llorente was also picked for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.heraldo.es/noticias/deportes/futbol/2022/11/11/en-directo-luis-enrique-da-este-viernes-sus-elegidos-para-el-reto-de-catar-1611767.html|title=Guillamón, Ansu Fati y Nico Williams, novedades en la lista de Luis Enrique para el Mundial, que deja fuera a Sergio Ramos|trans-title=Guillamón, Ansu Fati and Nico Williams, new in Luis Enrique's list for the World Cup, one that leaves Sergio Ramos out|newspaper=[[Heraldo de Aragón]]|language=es|date=11 November 2022|access-date=6 December 2022}}</ref> He only took part in one match in [[Qatar]], the 3–0 [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]] loss against [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] in the last 16.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63789751|title=Morocco 0–0 Spain (Morocco win 3–0 on penalties)|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|first=Shamoon|last=Hafez|date=6 December 2022|access-date=7 December 2022}}</ref>

Llorente was part of a 29-man preliminary squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rfef.es/en/noticias/euro-2024-provisional-squad|title=Euro 2024 provisional squad|publisher=Royal Spanish Football Federation|date=27 May 2024|access-date=7 June 2024}}</ref> However, he did not make the final cut.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rfef.es/en/noticias/final-spain-squad-for-the-euro-2024-finals|title=OFFICIAL {{!}} Final Spain squad for the Euro 2024 finals|publisher=Royal Spanish Football Federation|date=7 June 2024|access-date=7 June 2024}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Originally a [[defensive midfielder]] or a [[playmaker]] in front of a back four, Llorente is also capable of playing in more advanced positions such as a [[Central midfielder|central]] or [[box-to-box midfielder]]. At Atlético Madrid, under coach [[Diego Simeone]], he was also fielded out of his regular position, first on the right side of the midfield in a [[Formation (association football)#4–4–2|4–4–2 formation]] and later as a supporting [[Forward (association football)|forward]] in the same system.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://en.as.com/en/2020/02/15/football/1581764913_178012.html|title=Atlético's Marcos Llorente enjoying new role and relishing Liverpool clash|newspaper=Diario AS|first=Andy|last=Hall|date=15 February 2020|access-date=18 June 2020|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210228074932/https://en.as.com/en/2020/02/15/football/1581764913_178012.html|archive-date=28 February 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/heres-how-simeone-has-moulded-the-new-marcos-llorente|title=Here's how Simeone has moulded the new Marcos Llorente|publisher=Ghana Soccernet|date=10 June 2020|access-date=18 June 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/atletico-madrid/20200614/481772667930/marcos-llorente-saco-nota-en-su-examen-como-punta.html|title=Marcos Llorente sacó nota en su examen como punta|trans-title=Marcos Llorente passed in his forward test|newspaper=[[Mundo Deportivo]]|first=Walter|last=Zimmermann|language=es|date=14 June 2020|access-date=18 June 2020}}</ref>

At the conclusion of [[2019–20 La Liga|2019–20]], Llorente was the sixth fastest player in the competition, with his top running speed clocked at 35.09&nbsp;km/h.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://junipersports.com/marcos-llorente-in-the-top-10-league-sprinters|title=Marcos Llorente in the Top 10 League sprinters|publisher=Juniper Sports|date=22 July 2020|access-date=24 July 2020}}</ref> Apart from his physical attributes, such as pace, height, body fitness and stamina, his strengths also included excellent ball winning skills, visionary passing over both short and long distances, dribbling, first touch and shooting from just outside the penalty area, which led him to score several goals.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/laboratorio-datos/2020/07/21/5f15cc32ca4741ba3b8b4593.html|title=Marcos Llorente, la metamorfosis de un mediocentro reconvertido a delantero|trans-title=Marcos Llorente, the metamorphosis of a central midfielder turned forward|newspaper=Marca|language=es|date=21 July 2020|access-date=24 July 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.squawka.com/en/marcos-llorente-atletico-position-change-liverpool-anfield|title=Stunning Liverpool may have changed the course of Marcos Llorente's career|publisher=Squawka|date=23 July 2020|access-date=24 July 2020}}</ref> The following season, as Atlético went through a tactical switch, he was usually deployed as either a box-to-box or an [[attacking midfielder]] in a [[Formation (association football)#5–3–2|5–3–2]] or 3–4–2–1 formations. On occasion, he also filled in as a right [[Defender (association football)#Wing-back|wingback]] for his club,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/atletico-madrid/20210213/492017189499/llorente-ya-es-el-todocampista-mas-decisivo-de-laliga.html|title=Llorente ya es el 'todocampista' más decisivo de LaLiga|trans-title=Llorente is already LaLiga's most decisive "allfielder"|newspaper=Mundo Deportivo|first=Chema|last=G. Fuente|language=es|date=13 February 2021|access-date=17 February 2021}}</ref> or a right back in a four-man defence for the national team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-espana.net/2021/03/29/atletico-madrid-star-marcos-llorente-set-for-defensive-role-on-spain-duty|title=Atletico Madrid star Marcos Llorente set for defensive role on Spain duty|publisher=Football España|first=Feargal|last=Brennan|date=29 March 2021|access-date=14 April 2021}}</ref>

For his training attitude and patience, Llorente was praised by Simeone and [[Jorge Valdano]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://elpais.com/deportes/2018/12/28/actualidad/1545993223_461399.html|title=Marcos Llorente, marine y monje|trans-title=Marcos Llorente, marine and monk|newspaper=[[El País]]|first=Jorge|last=Valdano|language=es|date=28 December 2018|access-date=24 July 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.intothecalderon.com/2020/6/19/21292615/marcos-llorente-virtue-patience-atletico-real-madrid-diego-simeone-laliga|title=Marcos Llorente and the virtue of patience|publisher=[[SB Nation]]|first=Robbie|last=Dunne|date=19 June 2020|access-date=24 July 2020}}</ref>

==Personal life==
A boyhood supporter of Real Madrid,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2018/12/19/5c1ab165e5fdea70168b4571.html|title=The great success of Santiago Solari is called Marcos Llorente|newspaper=Marca|first1=José Félix|last1=Díaz|first2=Padraig|last2=Whelan|date=19 December 2018|access-date=22 December 2018}}</ref> Llorente has ties in his family to both football and the club. His father [[Paco Llorente|Francisco]] and great uncle [[Francisco Gento]] were [[Winger (association football)|wingers]], while his maternal grandfather [[Ramón Grosso]] was a forward.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://futbol.as.com/futbol/2015/10/17/primera/1445096623_689050.html|title=Debutó con el Madrid Marcos Llorente, sobrino-nieto de Gento|trans-title=Madrid debut for Marcos Llorente, grand nephew of Gento|newspaper=Diario AS|language=es|date=17 October 2015|access-date=17 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realmadrid.com/noticias/2014/04/marcos-llorente-seguir-los-pasos-de-mi-familia-es-un-orgullo-y-una-motivacion-extra|title=Marcos Llorente: "Seguir los pasos de mi familia es un orgullo y una motivación extra"|trans-title=Marcos Llorente: "To follow in the footsteps of my family is an honour and an extra motivation"|publisher=Real Madrid CF|language=es|date=9 April 2014|access-date=17 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://footballbiography.com/marcos-llorente-football-journey-legacy-pressure-triumph/|title=Carrying his family's football legacy: Inside Marcos Llorente's world|publisher=Football Biography|first=Hale|last=Hendrix|date=22 August 2024|access-date=4 April 2025}}</ref>

Late into his career, Llorente received criticism for promoting unconventional health practices, including a strict paleolithic diet and controversial views on sun exposure, drawing concern from medical professionals and the media.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/articles-video/llorente-criticized-for-comment-on-sun-and-skin-cancer-2024-06-19|title=Llorente criticized for comment on Sun and skin cancer|publisher=[[beIN Sports]]|date=19 June 2024|access-date=20 June 2025}}</ref>

